stability was carried out using CUSUM, CUSUMSQ and Chow test. Standardized regression
was used to find out the comparative or relative effects of the monetary policy instruments
(Monetary policy rate, Cash reserve ratio, and Exchange rate) on the target variable (Economic
growth,).T-statistics and F-statistic were used to carry out statistical significance at 95%
confidence level. Coefficient of multiple determinations (R2) was also used to judge the
strength of the estimated regression equation. Also, Durbin Watson statistic was used to test for
the presence of serial correlation (Autocorrelation), which is also common in time series
data. From the analysis of the model for both alternative sub periods, the coefficients of the
estimated regression (for both ARDL and VECM) are not the same in the two sub periods.
